{{see|Langer}}
==English==

===Noun===
'''langer'''

# (''County Cork ( the Rebel County) slang'') a [[disagreeable]] [[person]], an [[idiot]].
#:''See that langer over there?''
# The male member.
#:''I've an awfully small langer.''
# "Acting the..." the act of being disagreeable.
#:''Ignore him, he's only acting the langer.''
# "Langerated" the state of being remarkably drunk.
#:''I was langereted last Saturday night''
#:''I'm langers.'''
# "A langerload" - a large amount.

====Usage note====
The word can be used in several positions in the same sentence, though it rarely is.
eg "That langer was acting the langer after a langerload of drink and flashed his langer at me mate Noel. He's some langer, boy."
Which translates roughly as:
"That drunken lout was acting anti-socially after drinking rather a lot and exposed his penis to my friend Noel. He is quite the idiot."

